# Windows 11 Environment

This project runs on **Windows 11** with **PowerShell** as the default shell. Use Windows-native syntax for all terminal commands and paths.

## Paths

- Prefer **absolute Windows paths**: `C:\Users\MainUser\Documents\Repos\packplot\...`
- Use backslashes in paths, or forward slashes when quoting is simpler — both work in PowerShell
- Do **not** assume Unix paths (`/home/...`, `/tmp/...`); use `$env:TEMP` or `Join-Path` for temp dirs

## Shell Syntax

- Write commands for **PowerShell**, not bash/sh
- Chain with `;` or separate `Shell` invocations — do **not** rely on bash-only `&&`, `||`, or `export`
- Environment variables: `$env:NAME` (e.g. `$env:PATH`), not `$NAME` or `export NAME=...`
- Process substitution, bash heredocs (`<<'EOF'`), and `$(cat <<'EOF' ...)` **do not work** in PowerShell

```powershell
# ❌ BAD — bash syntax
export FOO=bar && cd /tmp && ls -la

# ✅ GOOD — PowerShell
$env:FOO = "bar"; Set-Location $env:TEMP; Get-ChildItem
```

## Common Command Mappings

| Avoid (Unix) | Use (Windows / PowerShell) |
|---|---|
| `which cmd` | `Get-Command cmd` or `where.exe cmd` |
| `rm -rf dir` | `Remove-Item -Recurse -Force dir` |
| `cp -r src dst` | `Copy-Item -Recurse src dst` |
| `mv a b` | `Move-Item a b` |
| `cat file` | `Get-Content file` |
| `touch file` | `New-Item -ItemType File file` |
| `grep pattern file` | `Select-String pattern file` |
| `find . -name "*.py"` | `Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter *.py` |
| `/dev/null` | `$null` |
| `sleep 5` | `Start-Sleep -Seconds 5` |

## Git & Multi-line Strings

For commit messages or PR bodies, use PowerShell here-strings instead of bash heredocs:

```powershell
git commit -m @"
Short summary line.

Optional body paragraph.
"@
```

## Python & Tooling

- Run project scripts via **uv**: `uv run pytest`, `uv run python script.py`
- Activate venv only when needed: `.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1`
- Line endings may be **CRLF**; do not assume LF-only tooling behavior

## Assumptions to Avoid

- No `sudo`, `apt`, `brew`, `chmod`, or `ln -s`
- Filesystem is **case-insensitive** by default — watch for case-only renames
- Prefer **native Windows builds** of tools; if a command fails, retry with PowerShell equivalents before assuming WSL
